The paper deals with optimization of robotic tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed algorithm involves exploiting the distinction between task space and configuration space, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The optimization of robot configurations and travel time also involves control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions benchmarking and experimental results, which suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques.
